<subSubSection id="C37A6519712CFFF2D9940C62FE700697" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDF3692712CFFF2D9940C62FE700697" blockId="5.[174,1232,780,1031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
Diagnosis. The species is characterized by the dorsally absent occipital carina; strongly and uniformly swollen clypeus; strongly twisted mandible, with hardly visible lower tooth; propodeum with weak lateromedian longitudinal carinae reaching well defined area apicalis; fore wing with vein 3 
<emphasis id="B914EA80712CFFF2DB3A0C03FD3206D6" box="[589,643,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">rs-m</emphasis>
absent; granulate metasomal tergites 1–2; weakly upcurved female ovipositor, about 1.9 times as long as the hind tibia length; and tyloids on male flagellomeres 5–9.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37A6519712CFFF2D9940CA3FB080157" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" type="distribution">
